AB  - This chapter examines how Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Big Data transform Environmental, Social, and Governance (ESG) due diligence in entrepreneurial finance. Traditional ESG assessments often rely on fragmented or outdated data, limiting reliability for startups and SMEs. AI techniques such as Natural Language Processing, machine learning, and predictive analytics analyze diverse, unstructured sources like financial statements, regulatory filings, and social media to deliver real-time ESG insights. The proposed framework improves transparency, risk detection, and regulatory compliance, aligning investments with sustainability goals. Case studies in venture capital and crowdfunding show significant gains in governance scores, investor engagement, and funding efficiency. Ethical issues including bias and greenwashing are mitigated through explainable AI, human-in-the-loop verification, and open ESG taxonomies.
