AB  - This thesis builds on the idea that whom you know matter in Venture Capital (VC) and explores VC networks with a focus on Europe from three angles: First, it confirms the wide-held belief that Europe's VC network is more fragmented than its US or Asia counterparts. Europe splits into regional startup ecosystems but has become increasingly interconnected. Second, it finds that being part of a tight-knit group of co-investors and - ideally unique - brokerage opportunities in the overall network lead to better outcomes. Lastly, it reveals how personal connections among venture capitalists shape decision-making, differentiating four collaboration archetypes and emphasizing trust and reciprocity.
