AB  - This study examines the relationship between entrepreneurial firms ties to external financing and the subsequent growth of these firms. We adopt a network perspective and focus on the financial network activity of entrepreneurial firms and empirically explore the connection between financial network composition and firm growth. We use a unique longitudinal dataset containing detailed information about the financial network activity of Swedish Biotech companies over 10 years.
