TI  - The Rise of Crowdfunding and Its Disruption of Traditional Entrepreneurial Finance
JO  - International Journal of Science and Research (IJSR)
PY  - 2025
AB  - Crowdfunding has emerged as a transformative force in entrepreneurial finance, offering startups and small businesses an alternative to traditional funding methods such as bank loans, angel investments, and venture capital. This paper explores the evolution of crowdfunding models (reward-based, equity-based, donation-based, and debt-based), their comparative advantages, and their disruptive impact on the financial ecosystem. Drawing from recent empirical studies and platform data, the research highlights how crowdfunding democratizes access to capital, validates product-market fit early, and enhances customer engagement. However, challenges such as regulatory constraints, fraud risk, and scalability remain. The paper concludes with a discussion on how traditional financial institutions are adapting to this new paradigm and offers policy and strategic recommendations for entrepreneurs, investors, and regulators.
