AB  - This chapter investigates the convergence of AI-driven sentiment analysis, customer experience, and entrepreneurial finance through a systematic bibliometric assessment. Based on 426 Scopus-indexed publications (1997–2025), it maps the intellectual, conceptual, and methodological contours of the field using descriptive indicators, co-occurrence analysis, thematic mapping, and longitudinal trends. The findings show a shift from early machine learning to deep learning and transformer models, with growing applications in fintech, crowdfunding, digital banking, and startup evaluation. Customer experience emerges as a key theme, linking user perception to venture success and financial decisions. Despite growth, the field remains fragmented, with limited integration of generative AI and large language models. By combining methodological trends with application-driven insights, the chapter traces the evolution of sentiment analysis in entrepreneurial finance and identifies future research directions at the intersection of AI, customer behavior, and digital finance.
