TI  - Corporate venture capital (CVC) investments and digital transformation: analysis of moderating effects based on industry level
JO  - Technology Analysis and Strategic Management
PY  - 2025
AB  - Although numerous studies have focused on the advantages and necessity of digital transformation, the discussion on how to drive digital transformation in firms appears even more crucial and essential. Following the resource-based view (RBV), this study examines the relationship between CVC investments and digital transformation. The results demonstrate that CVC plays a pivotal role in facilitating the digital transformation of incumbent firms, even after a series of robustness tests. Moreover, the moderating effects reveal that industry competition intensity and industry technological change negatively affect the relationship, while industry growth positively affects the relationship. CVC investments have a significantly positive influence on TDT (Technology-based digital transformation) and do not affect MDT (Market-based digital transformation). These findings expand our understanding of effectively facilitating the digital transformation of incumbent firms and provide theoretical and practical implications.
