AB  - Quantum computing offers transformative computational capabilities, disrupting traditional investment paradigms and reshaping venture capital (VC) strategies. This paper examines its economic impact on VC, highlighting advancements in cryptography, materials science, and AI that create opportunities for startups and alter risk-reward dynamics. By analyzing trends and case studies, we reveal how quantum innovation accelerates cycles, redefines valuations, and reshapes global competition, guiding investors, policymakers, and entrepreneurs in navigating the emerging quantum landscape.
