JO  - Apple Academic Press eBooks
PY  - 2025
AB  - Entrepreneurial finance represents a subgroup of corporate Finance which focuses on financing younger and privately owned firms. It is emergence as a research field is the result of a double interest from both entrepreneurship researchers and financiers. Cumming (2019) brings about the two differences in entrepreneurial finance and corporate finance. First difference is in terms of the information asymmetry that exists between the entrepreneur and the providers of finance spanning over the firm lifecycle. By virtue of the nature of asymmetry in information the investors in the entrepreneurial firms are usually intermediaries having intermediaries who make investments for others. The second difference is in terms of the resources owned by entrepreneurial firm in comparison to established firms in context of both tangible and intangible assets and human capital. The stakeholders in the financing of the startups or new ventures are the entrepreneur, organizations providing finance to the entrepreneur, funding sources for financing organizations and the country in which the startup is located.
