AB  - This chapter explores the systematic literature review (SLR) methodology as a cornerstone of academic research, with a specific focus on its application in entrepreneurial finance. It outlines the steps involved in conducting an SLR, emphasizing its role in synthesizing fragmented research, identifying gaps, and shaping theoretical frameworks. The chapter highlights the unique value of SLRs in interdisciplinary fields, offering transparency, objectivity, and reproducibility. While addressing practical challenges such as setting eligibility criteria and determining review boundaries, it provides practical guidance for researchers, particularly in entrepreneurial finance, to effectively use the method. It also offers criteria for evaluating review quality, aiding editors, reviewers, and authors. By comparing SLRs with alternative review methods, the chapter underscores their potential to advance knowledge and inform policy.
