AU  - Yari Schoenrock
TI  - Enhancing European tech competitiveness: the critical role of the capital markets union in late stage financing
JO  - Portuguese National Funding Agency for Science, Research and Technology (RCAAP Project by FCT)
PY  - 2025
AB  - This thesis examines the challenges European start-ups face in securing late stage financing and how Capital Markets Union reforms could address them. Based on interviews with industry experts and literature analysis, it identifies regulatory fragmentation, limited institutional investor participation and weak IPO markets as critical barriers. Key reforms recommended include the creation of an EU Inc. under a 28th regime, adapting Solvency II to encourage institutional investment, consolidating stock exchanges and creating specialized IPO segments for technology companies. In addition, experts highlight the need for a pan-European mindset among founders and investors. Implementing these measures can boost Europe's innovation, competitiveness and growth.
